Bishop David Oyedepo of Living Faith Church has said God’s choice would emerge the winner of next month’s presidential election. Oyedepo disclosed this while praying for Nigeria at Covenant University. According to Oyedepo: “Nigeria’s forthcoming election will be peaceful. There shall be no blood shedding, no blood will be shed. There shall be peace and God’s choice candidate will emerge to rule Nigeria. “Nigeria will enjoy good security again. There shall be peace on land, at sea, in the air and everywhere.” Oyedepo’s remark counters that of The Apostolic Church Nigeria that there would be bloodshed in the country. The Vice President of The Apostolic Church, N.O Awojide also predicted that government properties would be burnt, adding that Nigerians should expect riots.